OL,3,CSpeaker likely to survive Commons
OL,4,Cchaos despite SNP and Tory fury
OL,6,FSir Lindsay Hoyle caused uproar in the
OL,7,FCommons chamber when he
OL,8,Fcontroversially selected a Labour
OL,9,Famendment on the SNP's opposition day,
OL,10,Fbut still he clings on, ITV News
OL,11,FDeputy Political Editor Anushka
OL,12,FAsthana reports
OL,14,FIt feels as if the House of Commons
OL,15,FSpeaker will survive this week's
OL,16,Fpolitical chaos, but only just.
OL,18,FThe threat to Lindsay Hoyle's position
OL,19,Fseems to have dissipated somewhat
OL,20,Fduring the day.
