OL,6,FWednesday was supposed to be the SNP's
OL,7,Fday in parliament when they would
OL,8,Fforce other parties to vote on their
OL,9,Fmotion calling for a ceasefire in
OL,10,FIsrael and Gaza.
OL,12,FLabour didn't support the wording -
OL,13,Fthough did want a ceasefire. So they
OL,14,Flaid down an alternative amendment.
OL,16,FThen the government laid down theirs
OL,17,Fand the parliamentary convention said
OL,18,Fthe Speaker should allow a vote on the
OL,19,FSNP motion and then the government one
OL,20,Fonly.
