OL,6,F"I like him but he played high-stakes
OL,7,Fpolitics, and lost, badly."
OL,9,FMost upset were the SNP - with
OL,10,FWestminster leader Stephen Flynn -
OL,11,Fsaying he'd lost confidence in Hoyle.
OL,12,FHe - and then the party's chief whip,
OL,13,FOwen Thompson, went to see Hoyle today.
OL,15,FAfterwards, I spoke to Thompson who
OL,16,Fdescribed his frustration about the
OL,17,Fmayhem on a day that was meant to be
OL,18,Fabout giving a smaller party its voice.
