OL,6,FHe said the Speaker had promised him
OL,7,Fthat whatever happened the SNP would
OL,8,Fget a vote on their motion (but the
OL,9,Fwhole thing collapsed when the
OL,10,Fgovernment refused to vote on the
OL,11,FLabour amendment).
OL,13,FHe said he was considering Hoyle's
OL,14,Foffer of an emergency decade on Monday
OL,15,F- allowing the SNP to put forward its
OL,16,Fceasefire again for a vote (a move
OL,17,Fthat would again break with
OL,18,Fconvention).
