OL,6,FStarmer had argued that not letting
OL,7,FLabour put forward its own ceasefire
OL,8,Fmotion (meaning many would then be
OL,9,Faccused of opposing the policy by
OL,10,Fabstaining on the SNP's ceasefire call
OL,11,Fbecause of certain language) could
OL,12,Fresult in MPs facing abuse.
OL,14,FSome frontbenchers have faced nasty
OL,15,Fprotests over their failure to go
OL,16,Fharder on the question of Gaza.
